name: Assessment Review Register
description: Domain type for Assessment Review assets, which are created when an assessment is conducted on an asset and submitted for review.

name: BI Catalog
description: Domain that collects assets of BI systems

name: Business Dimensions
description: A set of Business Dimensions that categorize and describe Business Terms

name: Codelist
description: Any kind of data that is used solely to categorize other data found in a database, or solely for relating data in a database to information beyond the boundaries of the enterprise.

name: Data Usage Registry
description: A Collection of Data usage agreements and related Data structures

name: Glossary
description: A prioritized list of Business Terms, Acronyms and their meanings

name: Hierarchies
description: A Code list with a hierarchical structure in its Code Values

name: Logical Data Dictionary
description: Represents details of organizational data, independent of any particular technology and uses vocabulary of a business area to communicate with non-technical stakeholders

name: Mapping Domain
description: Groups Data Assets of the type Crosswalk (to map between Code Sets) and Mapping Specification (used to map between Data Structures).

name: Physical Data Dictionary
description: A collection of physical objects like Table, Column, file field, Views, APIs to describe how data is stored, arranged and related to each other in a data storage technology/location

name: Policy Domain
description: A set of policies and standards related to an organization

name: Report Catalog
description: A collection of reports and their definitions with the list of related Report attributes

name: Rulebook
description: A set of rules on the basis of which decisions are made and programs or policies are governed

name: Technology Asset Domain
description: An inventory of all Technology assets and their business benefits.
